reviews_data.review_text: The only place I know of in Charlotte that I can get Rose Milk Tea. My FAVORITE Milk Tea!!! I love this place! They have fantastic Chicken and Spring Rolls as well! A great place to meet friends or just vibe by yourself.

We absolutely love the food and service here. Prices are very good, portions are big and food is flavored to perfection. EVERY TIME we're in Charlotte we eat here multiple times, with pleasure. Its great for dine as well as takeout.
Nice staff clean restaurant delicious food

Awesome cozy place to hang out or work: boba tea and salted Vietnamese coffee was great, other boba drinks were awesome as well. Egg noodle stir-fried with beef is my favorite and have always been since the food truck days, all the dishes taste like something my dad would make me when I was younger, very nostalgic in flavor and always remind me of home. Support your locals people, and if you’re new to Charlotte or just visiting, I would highly recommend stopping by here to get a quick bite and some refreshing boba. Also they added a sweet dessert on the menu called Bingsu(a popular Korean shaved ice dessert), I got the mango bingsu with a cup of condensed milk to pour on top, absolutely majestic and bursting with freshness.

The bingsu was some of the best I’ve had!! It was so good! The service was great as well. The mango milk tea and mango jelly was also yummy. The food personally was just not for me. We ordered the beef pad Thai, shrimp fried rice, dumplings, summer roll, and Carolina Reaper wings. The summer roll was good. The dumplings were also very good.

It’s a 40 min drive here for me, but I would definitely come back just for the bingsu!

(Sorry the food pictures were taken after eating some)
Very good and fast to grab a lunch bite.

You can never go wrong with any of their teas or milkteas. Love their Lychee tea with Lychee jelly and the Strawberry Matcha Latte! We tried their Knife Cut noodles with beef and forgot to take a picture because I absolutely devoured it in minutes. So good!

Their kalbi banh mi is enough to make me want to go back three times a day. The bread, the fillings, their version of pate is soooooo good! I couldn’t stop talking about how good it was in between bites.

Today 5/2/2025 I purchased the knife cut stir fry both beef and shrimp & it gave me diarrhea 😩 within minutes after eating. Not sure if the meat was bad or what. It tasted good that was the only issue. I love the boba tea

A modern approach to the Asian fusion genre, Nguyen's Noodles adds a contemporary touch to the classical noodle dishes. "Give me a bowl of something good", that's all we want, right? Luckily for us, they deliver just that and more.

Starting from their humble beginnings of a food truck, they've transformed an old tea bar to a modern quick bite or to-go restaurant. They have their take on popular noodle dishes from the Asian regions and more. Adding fried favorites like fried tofu and chicken to French fries.

Their little patio space outside has a nice relaxing vibe allowing you to decompress from the craziness of the day. Sipping on a Vietnamese coffee (their House Speciality milk tea) with the spring breeze blowing, made us feel like we were sitting at a Paris cafe - albeit missing the baguette and macaroons. Maybe they can expand into this? No, actually, let's keep the simplicity.
I'll take that over the overwhelming dishes many Asian fusion restaurants try to push on us. Not charging exorbitant prices either is a plus. Focus on what you're good at, and you'll shine. I'm excited to see the progress of this young couples endeavors into the Charlotte restaurant scene.
Great service and food. The Bahn Mi is really good. Fries are perfectly crispy. Friendly staff. The tea is delicious. My wife and I love it.
Showed up for dinner at 840, they say they are open until 9 but they closed the kitchen at 830. I don't know if that's how the boss runs it or just the crew tonight. Not a good experience

Meh, not bad but there are more flavorful options in Steele Creek for both teas and noods. Service was friendly but not super aware of the business. My husband and I were the only guests in the building and we had placed our order and Sat at a table. While we were waiting a man came in and stood at the counter for 3-5 minutes before walking out without any acknowledgement. I would recommend Paris Bang Mi or Bonsai Thai for noodles over Nguyen's. I would recommend moji tea or 1368 sweet corner cafe for tea.
The teas are good the sandwiches are good the atmosphere is good everything is good and service is good just don't get ice cream
My family and I were visiting Charlotte and the service was very good . I got the vermicelli noodles and rose milk tea and it was delicious, we all enjoyed the food . :D
The pad thai was very tasty and hot. The banh mi (pork) was thr best I've had in Charlotte. The meat is awesome and there was enough pate to really taste it. Love it.
Loved my vermicelli
I love coming here, The food is fresh and delicious. The teas are also good.
The food was less than alright. Barely ate half of it. For the quality of the food, definitely overpriced. Don’t chance it, if you still go, don’t say nobody warned you.

I started following their ig page after I saw some bomb looking noodles and gave them a try. Boba is always fantastic 💖 most recently I tried the banh mi and it was DELISH and the summer rolls always HIT! Highly recommend.

Half noodles and half tea, Nguyen's is in the strip mall next to the office park. The reviews got me here and through the door. I'm glad I stayed.

My wife and I both chose Pad Thai, mine with chicken and hers without. A huge portion, served quite hot and tasty. My only complaint is that while it had flavor and plenty of peanut sauce, it needed some zing. Adding spice or even offering it as a condiment would have really helped here.

Green tea was delicious and I love that I was asked how much sugar. Pro tip: 25% is not enough.

I was satisfied with the portion and the taste. I'd eat here again, but I think I'd bring my sriracha sauce with me next time!

Wonderful meals, fine taste/texture. Most of the food was nice and hot! Will definitely come back again. Had a variety of dishes...

Photos speak for themselves...
I had the chicken vermecelli bowl with a boba tea and it was delicious! The staff was also very friendly and helped me pick a good tea flavor.
The shop is very clean, the staff is polite and friendly, and the bubble tea tastes great! I will definitely come again if I have the chance. Great value for the price!
The best boba smoothies and noodles for sure in charlotte. Just trust me 👍🏼
I love this place. I am so picky about how my boba but they get it just right! It’s not overly sweet and so refreshing! I’ve gone back 4 times in a row
I wasn't impressed with the pad thai or rice noodles as they were very dry.
The bubble teas are great! I did get nauseous with the popcorn chicken but it could be due to my food sensitivities.
I got the Vietnamese coffee with sea salt and with was absolutely delicious and refreshing! The service was great as well.

Prices and CS are awesome. A lot of places overcharge but they don't and the food is great! Really authentic! Plus the bubble teas are actually dairy free! A lot of places say they are but the mixes they use will have whey and casein in it, which is dairy. Here, you can request oat or almond milk as an alternative!

On Monday's there's happy hour were you get a free drink, got me a Thai tea, with an order of an entree. I didn't even know till I came in! They didn't have to tell me about it cause I probably would've paid extra for the drink and boba but the staff were super nice and helped me out!

I would definitely come again!

reviews_data.review_text: Loved everything about my visit. Food was excellent. Staff was friendly and courteous.  Clean. Nice little spot for quick bite. Nice selection of teas

I Generally Enjoy the Flavored Tea here, but for some reason when I get something to eat like Chicken Tenders or Noodles, I start getting Nauseous or an upset Stomach, this seems to happen every other time I Visit, My Cousin which i go with often will experience the same thing, has this been happening with anyone else?

The place is clean, modern, new and the service is nice. However, the food is just ‘meh’. It’s what you would cook at home by just mixing a few things together but overpriced here. The place has a very ‘cafe’ like feeling, and not a relaxing sit down to eat ambience. They give a free Bobba tea with an entree, but I would have rather liked just a good entree.
Food is great

1 star, very expensive and they gave us all to go boxes and even charged a $3 service on top of the tip which I didn’t know that fee was included until I saw my receipt. With all that we had to clear our table, very disappointed.

My FAVORITE BOBA SHOP + VIET FOOD! Love the variety of menu items and consistency with their entrees. Employees are super personable and offer great recommendations based off your palette. Would highly recommend the vermicelli bowl, knife cut noodles, popcorn chicken & thai coconut milk tea!! Best boba in CLT
Great place!

I don't say this lightly... the avocado boba tea was amazing, probably the best one I've had in a really long time!  I also got the knife cut noodles with tofu and the stir fry noodle with chicken and both were really good.  Will definitely be back!

The best bubble around

We were very happy with our food. Everything was freshly made, and the service was great. The place was clean and had a 99% sanitation grade, so that was reassuring. We definitely will be back to try other dishes and teas!

Best Pad Thai and bubba Thai Tea ever. Super friendly staff.

This place is really awesome.

Dumplings were delicious and the rose boba tea was on point. Definitely will be back.
Solid food and the coconut milk tea was great.
Yummy boba tea, especially the mango smoothie with boba. Friendly and convenient.

I’ve had their pad Thai before when they had their food truck, and it was very delicious and rich in flavor. Yesterday, I came to visit their restaurant and finally got to try their knife cut stir fry noodle. It was delicious, the noodles brings a different spin to the dish. Their basil popcorn chicken is always good, especially dipped in the sweet chili sauce they have. It’s worth giving them a try and you won’t regret it. You’ll definitely come back for more!
That Brian guy has very good customer service skills!

Delicious Avacado Smoothie with tapioca! My brother got a Oreo smoothie and really enjoyed it as well.

We did popcorn chicken, chicken fried rice and pad thai. Prices were very fair for how much food you get. The popcorn chicken tastes much fresher than any I've had before and the chicken fried rice was excellent. After adding a little bit of extra heat to the Pad Thai, it also was super nice!

Can't go wrong with giving this place a shot! I know if I lived closer, I'd be getting avacado smoothie cravings.

We looked in for the menu earlier in the day and promised to come back that evening. We're so glad we came back. All the fried rices were excellent.  We also enjoyed the wings and Thai tea. Can't wait to try some more on the menu.

Their noodles are delicious and so are the drinks! My favorite is the Thai green tea with boba. And let’s not forget about the popcorn chicken… if you haven’t tried it, you must!! I’m excited to try out their wings sometime soon. :)

Hope this place does well!  Not from here, just passing through on our way home.
Extremely happy with our teas,rice noodle with shrimp and our spring rolls.  The chicken fried rice was good, but I’ve had better.  Maybe needs more soy sauce?  The staff was friendly and accommodating.  Let us try the boba we had not had before😊.  I highly recommend the taro milk tea with crystal boba and the rose milk tea with boba and cheese.  It has average boba prices so be prepared.  All together pretty awesome and I wish we had one at home. Good luck!

Nguyen noodles has always been great to me from when they were in a truck to their brick and mortar store. Great service and even better food! The boba slushees are always refreshing after a workout and the spicy chili sauce is always a go to please come and check this out when your free!!!!

Nguyen's Noodles & Tea is the place to be for boba tea and a quick bite to eat. I got the avocado smoothie and it was very smooth & tasty. The popcorn chicken was yummy and come in a shareable size with your family & friends. 5/5 would recommend and come back here!
Cool little place definitely my new go to for boba and noodles. Clean and quick
Great customer service and even better food. Noodles were made to perfection.
WOW - Pad Thai was amazing.  Service was great and the ambience is awesome.  Will be going back again and again.
Amazing food, drinks and boba, and awesome co-workers who are extremely respectful and care for their customers!

Everything was delicious! The portion for the egg noodles was great and the homemade chili sauce is to die for. The creamy black milk tea is the perfect blend of tea and milk without being overly sweet. Definitely a place worth checking out!

Got some rice noodle stir fry with shrimp and some chicken tenders. Jasmine green tea with wintermelon to drink. Really great stuff all around, everything had just the right balance of flavors to let each ingredient stand out.

I ordered an avocado smoothie and chicken bites today. The smoothie was fresh, cold, and refreshing! Just what I needed on a sunny day! The chicken bites were at the right portion for the price you pay for it. It had a very distinct flavor thanks to the crispy basil that came with it. All in all, I'm glad we have a tea bar like this in Charlotte!
Cantaloupe yogurt smoothie was spectacular!! Perfect drink for a nice sunny day. The popcorn chicken and fries were also amazing. Highly recommend.

Paying $18 for two regular boba teas with up charge for oat milk since we’re vegan and can’t have cows milk just doesn’t seem worth it here. The teas were fine but nothing to write home about. But mostly just three stars because - I asked for less ice but still got regular amount filling half my cup and my husband and I got 1 tablespoon of boba pearls (see picture) which is significantly less than what we used to get with their previous management. If I’m paying almost $20, please make sure there is enough ingredients to account for that price. Quantity and quality seems unfortunately very different all of a sudden with this management change.

Just an amazing experience from start-to-finish! I was visiting from Chicago and I am so happy I stumbled upon this spot. The staff was incredibly friendly and down-to-earth, so the service was good. The food was even better! I could tell it was freshly prepared which is not always a guarantee. Highly recommend the popcorn chicken and fried rice. If you're in the area, it's definitely a must!
Their food was very good! I tried the popcorn chicken and black tea boba and needless to say it was amazing! Definitely Recommend!
My favorite is the chicken rice noodle stir fry! The chicken isn’t dry like most places I’ve tried, and I ordered the honey green tea with just the honey and it was a nice refresher.
The food and teas are amazing and the yum yum sauce is A1! The owner and staff were super cool and very friendly.
Definitely coming back! I’m picky with my food so I don’t eat out much but might be my new go-to lunch spot. Freshly prepared food, reasonably priced!

Such a treat! Great staff
Great Vietnamese coffee and housemade sauces <3
Love this place! The workers are nice and friendly and helped me decide on a drink to get, I also came back another day and got a chicken pad thai and it was one of the best things I ever had!
Great service, amazing drinks and delicious fried rice
The avocado smoothie w/ boba is a treat!  🤌🏽 Also, the pad thai is pretty good. Ask for extra peanuts 😎
Some of the best noodles I’ve ever had, I got the egg noodle stir fry & for my drink I got a Passionfruit Tea w/ mango jelly. Would definitely go back!
Great service and they are very nice! I love their stir fry! Chili oil is amazing as well. Black milk tea is great as well! I would definitely come back!
Food here is amazing! The beef fried rice with the yum yum sauce is a hit. They  Also have boba tea !!! I love this place!!!!
Great food. Good people. Good spot to grab a cold drink, some delicious two scoops ice cream, and some good noodles! The fried rice is the bomb too! I’ll continue to come back

The staff was friendly and accommodating.  Let us try the boba we had not had before😊.  I highly recommend the taro milk tea with crystal boba and the rose milk tea with boba and cheese.  It has average boba prices so be prepared.  All together pretty awesome and I wish we had one at home. Good luck!

Nguyen noodles has always been great to me from when they were in a truck to their brick and mortar store. Great service and even better food! The boba slushees are always refreshing after a workout and the spicy chili sauce is always a go to please come and check this out when your free!!!!

Nguyen's Noodles & Tea is the place to be for boba tea and a quick bite to eat. I got the avocado smoothie and it was very smooth & tasty. The popcorn chicken was yummy and come in a shareable size with your family & friends. 5/5 would recommend and come back here!
Cool little place definitely my new go to for boba and noodles. Clean and quick
Great customer service and even better food. Noodles were made to perfection.
WOW - Pad Thai was amazing.  Service was great and the ambience is awesome.  Will be going back again and again.
Amazing food, drinks and boba, and awesome co-workers who are extremely respectful and care for their customers!

Everything was delicious! The portion for the egg noodles was great and the homemade chili sauce is to die for. The creamy black milk tea is the perfect blend of tea and milk without being overly sweet. Definitely a place worth checking out!

Got some rice noodle stir fry with shrimp and some chicken tenders. Jasmine green tea with wintermelon to drink. Really great stuff all around, everything had just the right balance of flavors to let each ingredient stand out.

I ordered an avocado smoothie and chicken bites today. The smoothie was fresh, cold, and refreshing! Just what I needed on a sunny day! The chicken bites were at the right portion for the price you pay for it. It had a very distinct flavor thanks to the crispy basil that came with it. All in all, I'm glad we have a tea bar like this in Charlotte!
Cantaloupe yogurt smoothie was spectacular!! Perfect drink for a nice sunny day. The popcorn chicken and fries were also amazing. Highly recommend.

Paying $18 for two regular boba teas with up charge for oat milk since we’re vegan and can’t have cows milk just doesn’t seem worth it here. The teas were fine but nothing to write home about. But mostly just three stars because - I asked for less ice but still got regular amount filling half my cup and my husband and I got 1 tablespoon of boba pearls (see picture) which is significantly less than what we used to get with their previous management. If I’m paying almost $20, please make sure there is enough ingredients to account for that price. Quantity and quality seems unfortunately very different all of a sudden with this management change.

Just an amazing experience from start-to-finish! I was visiting from Chicago and I am so happy I stumbled upon this spot. The staff was incredibly friendly and down-to-earth, so the service was good. The food was even better! I could tell it was freshly prepared which is not always a guarantee. Highly recommend the popcorn chicken and fried rice. If you're in the area, it's definitely a must!
Their food was very good! I tried the popcorn chicken and black tea boba and needless to say it was amazing! Definitely Recommend!
My favorite is the chicken rice noodle stir fry! The chicken isn’t dry like most places I’ve tried, and I ordered the honey green tea with just the honey and it was a nice refresher.
The food and teas are amazing and the yum yum sauce is A1! The owner and staff were super cool and very friendly.
Definitely coming back! I’m picky with my food so I don’t eat out much but might be my new go-to lunch spot. Freshly prepared food, reasonably priced!

Such a treat! Great staff
Great Vietnamese coffee and housemade sauces <3
Love this place! The workers are nice and friendly and helped me decide on a drink to get, I also came back another day and got a chicken pad thai and it was one of the best things I ever had!
Great service, amazing drinks and delicious fried rice
The avocado smoothie w/ boba is a treat!  🤌🏽 Also, the pad thai is pretty good. Ask for extra peanuts 😎
Some of the best noodles I’ve ever had, I got the egg noodle stir fry & for my drink I got a Passionfruit Tea w/ mango jelly. Would definitely go back!
Great service and they are very nice! I love their stir fry! Chili oil is amazing as well. Black milk tea is great as well! I would definitely come back!
Food here is amazing! The beef fried rice with the yum yum sauce is a hit. They  Also have boba tea !!! I love this place!!!!
Great food. Good people. Good spot to grab a cold drink, some delicious two scoops ice cream, and some good noodles! The fried rice is the bomb too! I’ll continue to come back
